**The name of the program is PmergeMe**
The subject requires:
Only positive integers
No duplicates==>up to u!
Error handling
No invalid input
No overflow (must fit in int)








ğŸ”¹ Binary Search + Insert (Important Notes)

1)The binary search used here does not return â€œwhere the value existsâ€.
It returns the correct insertion position to keep the array sorted
(same behavior as lower_bound).

2)Even if the value already exists (duplicates):

Binary search returns the position where it should be inserted.

vector::insert() shifts elements to the right.

Nothing is overwritten.

The array remains sorted.

3)If binary search returns 0:

The value is smaller than all elements.

mainChain.insert(mainChain.begin(), value);

All elements shift right.

The new value becomes the first element.

4)Difference between assignment and insert:

mainChain[pos] = value;      // âŒ overwrites
mainChain.insert(begin+pos, value);  // âœ… shifts and inserts

5)std::vector::insert():

Shifts elements to the right.

Reallocates memory if needed.

Never deletes existing values.